-- Deals of the day- Mergers and acquisitions
-- 
-- Thu Apr 10, 2014 06:00AM EDT
-- None



April 10 (Reuters) - The following bids, mergers, acquisitions and disposals were reported by 1000 GMT on Thursday:

** India's Piramal Enterprises Ltd <PIRA.NS> said on Thursday that it agreed to sell an about 11 percent stake it owns in the Indian unit of Vodafone Group Plc <VOD.L> to the British group for 89 billion rupees ($1.48 billion). [ID:nL3N0N21K5]  ** Asahi Group Holdings Ltd <2502.T> said on Thursday that it would buy the Southeast Asian dairy operations of Etika International Holdings Ltd <ETIK.SI> for $329 million. [ID:nT9N0MP01N]  ** The Philippines' International Container Terminal Services Inc <ICT.PS> said on Thursday that it had agreed to operate, develop and expand Iraq's largest port facilities and invest $130 million in the first phase of the deal. [ID:nL3N0N20T0]  ** Several large hedge funds doubled down on Puerto Rico in last month's giant bond sale despite the U.S. territory's financial struggles, the Wall Street Journal reported, citing confidential documents reviewed by the newspaper. Och-Ziff Capital Management <OZM.N>, Paulson & Co, Fir Tree Partners, Perry Capital LLC and Brigade Capital Management each bought more than $100 million of the bonds, according to a list of buyers of the sale, the newspaper said. [ID:nL3N0N21AN]  ** Belgian chemicals group Solvay <SOLB.BR> said on Thursday that it had agreed to sell its European PVC compound business Benvic Europe to U.S. investment firm Open Gate Capital.[ID:nL6N0N20XM]  ** Israeli energy and insurance conglomerate Delek Group <DLEKG.TA> said on Thursday that it was in advanced talks to sell its U.S. insurance business Republic Group. [ID:nL6N0N21IM]